content:
OmniScript handles data and external integrations through Action, Group, and Input elements. Elements use Omnistudio Data Mappers, Integration Procedures, HTTP Actions, and Apex to load, transform, and post data.

Load Data into OmniScript Elements: Populate OmniScript elements with data using Omnistudio Data Mappers, Integration Procedures, HTTP Actions, URL parameters, or Apex.

Access OmniScript Data JSON with Merge Fields: Enable OmniScript elements to access data JSON using merge fields.

Set Values in an OmniScript: Use the Set Values action to set element values, rename JSON nodes, create dynamic values, and concatenate data.

Manipulate JSON with the Send/Response Transformations Properties: Specify and transform input and output JSON of OmniScripts or Integration Procedures.

Create Formula Fields in an OmniScript: Create expressions to set calculated values using a Formula or Aggregate element.

Create and Update Data from OmniScripts: Post data to Salesforce and external databases using action elements that integrate Omnistudio Data Mappers, Integration Procedures, external calls, and Apex.

Integrate DocuSign with OmniScripts: Enable users to sign DocuSign forms in an OmniScript or email a copy of the document to sign at their convenience.
title: OmniScript Data and External Integrations
